parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brakes can cause the vehicle to skid or pull to one side, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on wet roads.
symptoms: The vehicle takes longer to stop
the front brakes do not hold
the vehicle skids or pulls to one side when braking
unusual sounds from the front end
visible damage to the upper frame or A-frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes lock up
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail or lock up, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brakes lock up
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes fail to respond.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient cooling system capacity can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to engine components, reduced engine performance, and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge rises to the red zone
the temperature warning light illuminates
the engine overheats
the coolant level drops
the coolant leaks
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Manual Transmission Failure in Diesel Engine Trucks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents, loss of control, or strandings, especially when towing or hauling heavy loads.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the transmission grinds or makes unusual noises when shifting
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the transmission jumps out of gear
the vehicle loses power or stalls
difficulty shifting into gear
especially when cold.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Deteriorated Fuel Line Causing Engine Compartment Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A deteriorated fuel line can cause fuel leakage, leading to an engine compartment fire, which can result in serious injury, fatalities, or significant vehicle damage.
symptoms: Fuel smell or leak in the engine compartment
visible signs of fuel leakage
engine compartment fire
warning lights or alarms indicating a fuel system issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt buckle can prevent the seat belt from properly restraining the occupant, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch or unlatch
the seat belt buckle is stuck
the seat belt buckle is loose
the seat belt warning light is illuminated
the seat belt is unable to be secured.
